    "Question": {
      "content": "1 electron volt (1eV) is equivalent to:",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "1.6 × 10⁻¹⁹ N",
        "1.6 × 10⁻¹⁹ J",
        "1.6 × 10⁻¹⁹ C",
        "1.6 × 10⁻¹⁹ A"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "1.6 × 10⁻¹⁹ J"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "1 <b>electron volt</b> (eV) is the energy gained by an electron when moved through a 1V potential difference.<br><br>\\(1\\,eV = e \\times 1\\,V = (1.6\\times10^{-19}\\,C)(1\\,V) = 1.6\\times10^{-19}\\,J\\)<br><br>It’s a tiny unit of energy used in atomic and particle physics."
    },
