    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 44 @ 2016/2017",
    "Question": {
      "content": "What capacitance is needed to store enough energy to power a 50W bulb for 30 minutes at 200V?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "90F",
        "45F",
        "6F",
        "9F"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "45F"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<b>Step 1:</b> Energy needed \\(E = P \\times t = 50W \\times 1800s = 90,000J\\).<br><b>Step 2:</b> Using \\(E = \\frac{1}{2}CV^2\\), solve for \\(C = \\frac{2E}{V^2} = 45F\\)."
    },
